[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hockey World League Semi-Final: Scotland lose play-off to South Korea

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scotland men lost their Hockey World League Semi-Final ninth/10th-place play-off against South Korea as they were undone by clinical finishing.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Derek Forsyth's men, playing for the first time at this level, scored first at Lee Valley through Tim Atkins but trailed 2-1 after the first quarter.
Alan Forsyth, Gordon McIntyre and Kenny Bain went close but the Blue Sticks trailed 6-1 going into the final quarter at Lee Valley in London.
Bain's two late goals made it 6-3.
Scotland drew one and lost three of their Pool B matches and missed the chance to reach the quarter-finals and a possible World Cup place.
